        <td bgcolor='black' valign=top width='100' nowrap><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'><b>The VISION tm</b></font></td>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> I have been working about 70 hours a week trying to get some things done at my job so I haven't been able to put the finishing touches on the site.  I am sorry for that, but work takes 1st priority.  I hope you all understand.  After working all the time, the last thing I want to do is work some more so I haven't been coding.  Things should slow down drastically very soon at my job front and I will start investing the time needed to finalize the site.</P><P>On a positive note, I got my monk to level 40 and decided that I have been living a lie.  I sold off all my monk gear last night and I am back full time to my beloved necro.  </P><P>Now for my soapbox...</P><P>I think the changes Verant has been making lately has shown a new attitude towards their client base.  They seem to be focusing on not fixing the game but making it more enjoyable for the masses and honestly after running this site for years that is a welcome surprise.  I know a lot of you are going to say we were nerfed, Verant sucks, or the latest patch sucks, but look at what they have added for us.  The Focus Items are very nice, the lower summon corpse spell will help our younger necros, the perm focus items, no more staring into the book for days on end while medding, fixed hell levels, no item or exp loss for level 9 and below, the ancient spell lines that are being added, they fixed several spells for us so they are not night time only, the chat channels are wonderful, no more losing messages while zoning, they allowed our gnecro brethren to also play shadowknights... the list goes on.  I think this is a time we should give Verant their due because I personally feel they deserve it.  The latest patch did not address all issues with the necro class or the game in general but it is a wonderful start.  This is the first time I have seen a patch and I was extremely excited.  I applaud you Verant for the last patch and hope this isn't an exception but a rule for the future.</P><P>I am he who writes the law and spreads the VISION tm.</font></td>
